  "text": "The family was split by Maguire ( , 1965 into two subfamilies (Saxofridericioideae and Rapateoideae) based on the number of ovules per carpel, placentation type, and morphology of seed, pollen and inflorescence . Givnish et al. (2000) pointed out that at least Rapateoideae is paraphyletic in their molecular studies. Later, a new classification for the family based on chloroplast analyses, showing three well supported subfamilies (Rapateoideae, Saxifridericioideae and Monotremoideae), was presented by [CITATION_1] .",
